---
/** Example page for @lexingtonthemes/astro-image-inspector */
---
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Image Inspector Example</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Image Inspector Example</h1>
    <p>Run <code>npm run dev</code>, open the dev toolbar (hover bottom of page), click "Image Inspector", then hover each image below.</p>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Normal size (400×300 rendered, same intrinsic)</h2>
      <img
        src="https://placehold.co/400x300/purple/white?text=400x300"
        alt="Placeholder"
        width="400"
        height="300"
      />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Oversized source (4000×3000 image shown at 200×150)</h2>
      <img
        src="https://placehold.co/4000x3000/blue/white?text=4000x3000"
        alt="Oversized"
        width="200"
        height="150"
      />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Upscaled (100×100 image shown at 300×300)</h2>
      <img
        src="https://placehold.co/100x100/green/white?text=100x100"
        alt="Upscaled"
        width="300"
        height="300"
      />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. No width/height (relies on intrinsic size)</h2>
      <img
        src="https://placehold.co/320x180/red/white?text=no+dimensions"
        alt="No dimensions"
      />
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
